dcterms:description: A large freely-available dataset of 57,786 ICU hospital admissions of 46,476 patients from one US hospital between 2001-2012, containing structured data like laboratory measurements, vital signs, patient demographics, and clinical diagnostic and procedure codes.
dcterms:title: MIMIC-III

dcterms:description: The International Statistical Classification of Diseases and Related Health Problems version 9 (ICD9) was used for coding patient conditions and the procedures received, consisting of about 13,000 unique codes in varying levels of detail.
dcterms:title: ICD9

dcterms:description: A dataset containing 49,002 admissions of 38,402 patients with 822,047 codes recorded, focusing on codes that appeared at least 50 times.
dcterms:title: Admissions Dataset
